Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with designing algorithms for a specific problem in the streaming model.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper provides lower bounds on the space requirements for randomized approximation algorithms.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses information-theoretic techniques to derive the lower bounds.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial objects (palindromes) and their properties.
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes new algorithms for the problem.
